{{Lunisolar October}} 
'''October 13''' is the 13th day of month {{ill|October (Lunisolar)|ja|10月 (旧暦)|lt=Kannazuki|1=Kannazuki|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} , the 10th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} . It's {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}  day is {{ill|Butsumetsu|ja|仏滅|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} .
== Events ==
* {{ill|Keikō Tennō|ja|景行天皇|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 27th year（{{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}  {{ill|97|ja|97|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}  {{ill|November 5|ja|11月5日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ） – {{ill|Keikō Tennō|ja|景行天皇|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}  ordered the young prince (later known as {{ill|Yamato Takeru|ja|日本武尊|1=Yamato Takeru|lt=Prince Yamato Takeru|3=ヤマトタケル|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ) to subdue the Kumano (熊襲).
* {{ill|Genwa (Japan)|ja|元和|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 9th year (1623, December 4) – ({{placeholder: Great Martyrdom of Edo}} )
* {{ill|Bunka (era)|ja|文化 (元号)|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 1st year（{{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}  {{ill|1804|ja|1804|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}  {{ill|November 14|ja|11月14日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ） – {{ill|Kawaoka Seishū|ja|華岡青洲|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}  achieved Japan’s first successful surgery using anesthesia.<ref>…</ref>
* {{ill|Meiji|ja|明治|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 1st year（{{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}  {{ill|1868|ja|1868|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}  {{ill|November 26|ja|11月26日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ） – The Meiji Emperor entered Edo Castle, renaming it “Tokyo Castle” and establishing the Imperial Palace.
