'''October 13''' is the 13th day of month {{ill|October (Lunisolar)|ja|10月 (旧暦)|lt=October (Kannazuki)|1=Kannazuki|2=ja|3=10月 (旧暦)|1=Kannazuki|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/October (Lunisolar)|13=User:Immanuelle/Kannazuki|qq=}} , the 10th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}} . It's {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokuyō|qq=}}  day is {{ill|Butsumetsu|ja|仏滅|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Butsumetsu|qq=}} .
== Events ==
* [[:en:Emperor Keikō|Keikō Tennō]] 27th year（[[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]]  [[:en:97 (number)|97]]  [[:en:November 5|November 5]] ） – [[:en:Emperor Keikō|Keikō Tennō]]  ordered the young prince (later known as {{ill|Yamato Takeru|ja|日本武尊|1=Yamato Takeru|lt=Prince Yamato Takeru|3=ヤマトタケル|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yamato Takeru|13=User:Immanuelle/Yamato Takeru|qq=}} ) to subdue the Kumano (熊襲).
* [[:en:Yuanhe|Genwa (Japan)]] 9th year (1623, December 4) – ({{placeholder: Great Martyrdom of Edo|qq=}} )
* [[:en:Bunka|Bunka (era)]] 1st year（[[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]]  {{ill|1804|ja|1804|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1804|qq=}}  [[:en:November 14|November 14]] ） – [[:en:Hanaoka Seishū|Kawaoka Seishū]]  achieved Japan’s first successful surgery using anesthesia.<ref>…</ref>
* [[:en:Meiji era|Meiji era]] 1st year（[[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]]  {{ill|1868|ja|1868|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1868|qq=}}  [[:en:November 26|November 26]] ） – The Meiji Emperor entered Edo Castle, renaming it “Tokyo Castle” and establishing the Imperial Palace.
== Births ==
* [[:en:Wadō (era)|Wadō]] 2nd year（[[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]]  {{ill|709|ja|709|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/709|qq=}}  [[:en:November 18|November 18]] ） – Emperor [[:en:Emperor Kōnin|Kōnin]] , the 49th emperor († {{ill|781|ja|781|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/781|qq=}} ).

== Deaths ==
* [[:en:Kangi|Kankō]] 3rd year（[[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]]  {{ill|1231|ja|1231|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1231|qq=}}  [[:en:November 6|November 6]] ） – Emperor [[:en:Emperor Tsuchimikado|Tsuchimikado]] , the 83rd emperor (* {{ill|1195|ja|1195|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1195|qq=}} ).
* [[:en:Keian|Keian]] 2nd year（[[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]]  {{ill|1649|ja|1649|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1649|qq=}}  [[:en:November 15|November 15]] ） – [[:en:Konoe Nobuhiro|Konoe Nobuhiro]] , a court noble and regent (* {{ill|1599|ja|1599|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1599|qq=}} ).
* [[:en:Tenpō|Tenpō]] 12nd year（[[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]]  {{ill|1841|ja|1841|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1841|qq=}}  [[:en:November 23|November 23]] ） – [[:en:Watanabe Kazan|Watanabe Kasansan]] , a Dutch studies scholar and painter (* {{ill|1793|ja|1793|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1793|qq=}} ).

